sec.p:
The evaluation of sealing performance in terms of leakage and friction requires the computation of the film thickness and pressure distribution in the contact, which is based on the theory of (elasto) hydrodynamic lubrication represented by the Reynolds equation. The further main assumptions are usually made in treating reciprocating rod seals:


transient effects are ignored (applicable only for long stroking lengths, compared with the sealing-contact size);

the fluid is considered to be Newtonian;

the rubber is modelled as a non-linear elastic material;

the viscoelasticity is neglected; and

the seal is axisymmetric.
